definitions.definition: The traditional municipal building of a Scottish town or burgh, usually including a meeting-hall, court, prison and (eponymically) a place for the receipt of taxes, duties and fines.
labels: In this sense usually spelt tolbooth
label_groups: In this sense usually spelt tolbooth

main_definition: ( Scotland ) ( In this sense usually spelt tolbooth ) The traditional municipal building of a Scottish town or burgh, usually including a meeting-hall, court, prison and (eponymically) a place for the receipt of taxes, duties and fines.
